---
title: Hey, Honey! Salmon with Potato Wedges & Zesty Green Beans
description: Fishing for a delicious, sea-faring meal? We’ve got just the thing. Here, spice-rubbed salmon fillets are seared until crisp-skinned and flaky, then drizzled with a lemony, buttery honey Dijon sauce. They’re paired with tender roasted potato wedges and zesty green beans for a meal that is as elegant as it is delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6113d8a40dbe48785c37b3f5-95c14323.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hey-honey-salmon-6113d8a40dbe48785c37b3f5-70c1b7ef.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 230 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hey-honey-salmon-6113d8a40dbe48785c37b3f5
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest and quarter
@Lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%tsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.
(For 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven.

Carefully toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on empty side with a drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting
and add green beans to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack and roast until veggies are browned and tender,
~{12-15%minutes} more.

Toss roasted green beans with salt, pepper, and lemon zest to taste.

Meanwhile, pat @Salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining
@Fry Seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon
skin sides down and cook until browned and crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and
cook until salmon is opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer salmon to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Add @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce}, @water{2%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon
juice to same pan over medium heat; simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and
pepper to taste.

Divide salmon, potato wedges, and green beans between plates. Spoon sauce over
salmon. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.